Package edu.uci.ics.jung.random.generators

Provides a series of methods for generating new graphs with various properties.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
EvolvingGraphGenerator An interface for algorithms that generate graphs that evolve over time
GraphGenerator An interface for algorithms that generate graphs
 

Class Summary
BarabasiAlbertGenerator Simple evolving scale-free random graph generator.
EppsteinPowerLawGenerator Graph generator that generates undirected sparse graphs with power-law distributions.
ErdosRenyiGenerator Random Generator of Erdos-Renyi "binomial model"
KleinbergSmallWorldGenerator Graph generator that produces a random graph with small world properties.
Lattice1DGenerator Simple generator of an n x 1 lattice where each vertex is incident with each of its 2 neighbors (except possibly for the vertices on the edge depending upon whether the lattice is specified to be toroidal or not).
Lattice2DGenerator Simple generator of an n x n lattice where each vertex is incident with each of its 4 neighbors (except possibly for the vertices on the edge depending upon whether the lattice is specified to be toroidal or not).
SimpleRandomGenerator Simple graph generator where |V| vertices are generated and |E| random edges chosen pairwise uniformly
WattsBetaSmallWorldGenerator WattsBetaSmallWorldGenerator is a graph generator that produces a small world network using the beta-model as proposed by Duncan Watts.
 

Package edu.uci.ics.jung.random.generators Description

Provides a series of methods for generating new graphs with various properties.
